#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.61"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.61:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.61:0.2"
msgid "7. Pattakammavagga "
msgstr "7. Deeds of Substance "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.61:0.3"
msgid "61. Pattakammasutta "
msgstr "61. Deeds of Substance "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an4.61:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then the householder Anāthapiṇḍika went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.66, sc2
msgctxt "an4.61:2.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, gahapati, dhammā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā dullabhā lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "“Householder, these four things that are likable, desirable, and agreeable are hard to get in the world. "

msgctxt "an4.61:2.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "an4.61:2.3"
msgid "Bhogā me uppajjantu sahadhammenāti, ayaṃ paṭhamo dhammo iṭṭho kanto manāpo dullabho lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "The first thing is the wish: ‘May wealth come to me by legitimate means!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an4.61:3.1"
msgid "Bhoge laddhā sahadhammena yaso me āgacchatu saha ñātīhi saha upajjhāyehīti, ayaṃ dutiyo dhammo iṭṭho kanto manāpo dullabho lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "The second thing, having got wealth by legitimate means, is the wish: ‘May fame come to me, together with my family and teachers.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an4.61:4.1"
msgid "Bhoge laddhā sahadhammena yasaṃ laddhā saha ñātīhi saha upajjhāyehi ciraṃ jīvāmi dīghamāyuṃ pālemīti, ayaṃ tatiyo dhammo iṭṭho kanto manāpo dullabho lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "The third thing, having got wealth and fame, is the wish: ‘May I live long, keeping alive for a long time!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an4.61:5.1"
msgid "Bhoge laddhā sahadhammena yasaṃ laddhā saha ñātīhi saha upajjhāyehi ciraṃ jīvitvā dīghamāyuṃ pāletvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjāmīti, ayaṃ catuttho dhammo iṭṭho kanto manāpo dullabho lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "The fourth thing, having got wealth, fame, and long life, is the wish: ‘When my body breaks up, after death, may I be reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm!’ "

msgctxt "an4.61:5.2"
msgid "Ime kho, gahapati, cattāro dhammā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā dullabhā lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "These are the four things that are likable, desirable, and agreeable, but hard to get in the world. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an4.61:6.1"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho, gahapati, catunnaṃ dhammānaṃ iṭṭhānaṃ kantānaṃ manāpānaṃ dullabhānaṃ lokasmiṃ cattāro dhammā paṭilābhāya saṃvattanti. "
msgstr "These next four things lead to the getting of those four things. "

msgctxt "an4.61:6.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "an4.61:6.3"
msgid "Saddhāsampadā, sīlasampadā, cāgasampadā, paññāsampadā. "
msgstr "Accomplishment in faith, ethics, generosity, and wisdom. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an4.61:7.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, gahapati, saddhāsampadā? "
msgstr "And what is accomplishment in faith? "

msgctxt "an4.61:7.2"
msgid "Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako saddho hoti, saddahati tathāgatassa bodhiṃ: "
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple has faith in the Realized One’s awakening: "

msgctxt "an4.61:7.3"
msgid "‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi, satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti. "
msgstr "‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’ "

msgctxt "an4.61:7.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, gahapati, saddhāsampadā. "
msgstr "This is called accomplishment in faith. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an4.61:8.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, gahapati, sīlasampadā? "
msgstr "And what is accomplishment in ethics? "

msgctxt "an4.61:8.2"
msgid "Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti … pe … surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭivirato hoti. "
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, lie, or take alcoholic drinks that cause negligence. "

msgctxt "an4.61:8.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, gahapati, sīlasampadā. "
msgstr "This is called accomplishment in ethics. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an4.61:9.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, gahapati, cāgasampadā? "
msgstr "And what is accomplishment in generosity? "

msgctxt "an4.61:9.2"
msgid "Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako vigatamalamaccherena cetasā agāraṃ ajjhāvasati muttacāgo payatapāṇi vosaggarato yācayogo dānasaṃvibhāgarato. "
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple lives at home rid of the stain of stinginess, freely generous, open-handed, loving to let go, committed to charity, loving to give and to share. "

msgctxt "an4.61:9.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, gahapati, cāgasampadā. "
msgstr "This is called accomplishment in generosity. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.67, sc10
msgctxt "an4.61:10.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, gahapati, paññāsampadā? "
msgstr "And what is accomplishment in wisdom? "

msgctxt "an4.61:10.2"
msgid "Abhijjhāvisamalobhābhibhūtena, gahapati, cetasā viharanto akiccaṃ karoti, kiccaṃ aparādheti. "
msgstr "When your heart is mastered by covetousness and immoral greed, you do what you shouldn’t, and fail to do what you should. "

msgctxt "an4.61:10.3"
msgid "Akiccaṃ karonto kiccaṃ aparādhento yasā ca sukhā ca dhaṃsati. "
msgstr "Your fame and happiness are crushed. "

msgctxt "an4.61:10.4"
msgid "Byāpādābhibhūtena, gahapati, cetasā viharanto akiccaṃ karoti, kiccaṃ aparādheti. "
msgstr "When your heart is mastered by ill will … "

msgctxt "an4.61:10.5"
msgid "Akiccaṃ karonto kiccaṃ aparādhento yasā ca sukhā ca dhaṃsati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.61:10.6"
msgid "Thinamiddhābhibhūtena, gahapati, cetasā viharanto akiccaṃ karoti kiccaṃ aparādheti. "
msgstr "dullness and drowsiness … "

msgctxt "an4.61:10.7"
msgid "Akiccaṃ karonto kiccaṃ aparādhento yasā ca sukhā ca dhaṃsati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.61:10.8"
msgid "Uddhaccakukkuccābhibhūtena, gahapati, cetasā viharanto akiccaṃ karoti, kiccaṃ aparādheti. "
msgstr "restlessness and remorse … "

msgctxt "an4.61:10.9"
msgid "Akiccaṃ karonto kiccaṃ aparādhento yasā ca sukhā ca dhaṃsati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.61:10.10"
msgid "Vicikicchābhibhūtena, gahapati, cetasā viharanto akiccaṃ karoti, kiccaṃ aparādheti. "
msgstr "doubt, you do what you shouldn’t, and fail to do what you should. "

msgctxt "an4.61:10.11"
msgid "Akiccaṃ karonto kiccaṃ aparādhento yasā ca sukhā ca dhaṃsati. "
msgstr "Your fame and happiness are crushed. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "an4.61:11.1"
msgid "Sa kho so, gahapati, ariyasāvako abhijjhāvisamalobho cittassa upakkilesoti, iti viditvā abhijjhāvisamalobhaṃ cittassa upakkilesaṃ pajahati. "
msgstr "Knowing that ‘covetousness and immoral greed are corruptions of the mind’, that noble disciple gives them up. "

msgctxt "an4.61:11.2"
msgid "Byāpādo cittassa upakkilesoti, iti viditvā byāpādaṃ cittassa upakkilesaṃ pajahati. "
msgstr "Knowing that ‘ill will …’ … "

msgctxt "an4.61:11.3"
msgid "Thinamiddhaṃ cittassa upakkilesoti, iti viditvā thinamiddhaṃ cittassa upakkilesaṃ pajahati. "
msgstr "‘dullness and drowsiness …’ … "

msgctxt "an4.61:11.4"
msgid "Uddhaccakukkuccaṃ cittassa upakkilesoti, iti viditvā uddhaccakukkuccaṃ cittassa upakkilesaṃ pajahati. "
msgstr "‘restlessness and remorse …’ … "

msgctxt "an4.61:11.5"
msgid "Vicikicchā cittassa upakkilesoti, iti viditvā vicikicchaṃ cittassa upakkilesaṃ pajahati. "
msgstr "‘doubt is a corruption of the mind’, that noble disciple gives it up. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "an4.61:12.1"
msgid "Yato ca kho, gahapati, ariyasāvakassa abhijjhāvisamalobho cittassa upakkilesoti, iti viditvā abhijjhāvisamalobho cittassa upakkileso pahīno hoti. "
msgstr "When a noble disciple has given up these things, "

msgctxt "an4.61:12.2"
msgid "Byāpādo cittassa upakkilesoti, iti viditvā byāpādo cittassa upakkileso pahīno hoti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.61:12.3"
msgid "Thinamiddhaṃ cittassa upakkilesoti, iti viditvā thinamiddhaṃ cittassa upakkileso pahīno hoti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.61:12.4"
msgid "Uddhaccakukkuccaṃ cittassa upakkilesoti, iti viditvā uddhaccakukkuccaṃ cittassa upakkileso pahīno hoti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.61:12.5"
msgid "Vicikicchā cittassa upakkilesoti, iti viditvā vicikicchā cittassa upakkileso pahīno hoti. "
msgstr " "

#. VAR: āpātadaso → āpāthadaso (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: paññāsampanno → hāsapañño (mr)
msgctxt "an4.61:12.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, gahapati, ariyasāvako mahāpañño puthupañño āpātadaso paññāsampanno. "
msgstr "they’re called ‘a noble disciple of great wisdom, of widespread wisdom, who sees what matters, and is accomplished in wisdom’. "

msgctxt "an4.61:12.7"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, gahapati, paññāsampadā. "
msgstr "This is called accomplishment in wisdom. "

msgctxt "an4.61:12.8"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho, gahapati, catunnaṃ dhammānaṃ iṭṭhānaṃ kantānaṃ manāpānaṃ dullabhānaṃ lokasmiṃ ime cattāro dhammā paṭilābhāya saṃvattanti. "
msgstr "These are the four things that lead to the getting of the four things that are likable, desirable, and agreeable, but hard to get in the world. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "an4.61:13.1"
msgid "Sa kho so, gahapati, ariyasāvako uṭṭhānavīriyādhigatehi bhogehi bāhābalaparicitehi sedāvakkhittehi dhammikehi dhammaladdhehi cattāri pattakammāni kattā hoti. "
msgstr "There are four deeds of substance that a noble disciple does with the legitimate wealth he has earned by his efforts and initiative, built up with his own hands, gathered by the sweat of the brow. "

msgctxt "an4.61:13.2"
msgid "Katamāni cattāri? "
msgstr "What four? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.61:13.3"
msgid "Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako uṭṭhānavīriyādhigatehi bhogehi bāhābalaparicitehi sedāvakkhittehi dhammikehi dhammaladdhehi attānaṃ sukheti pīṇeti sammā sukhaṃ pariharati. "
msgstr "To start with, with his legitimate wealth he makes himself happy and pleased, keeping himself properly happy. "

msgctxt "an4.61:13.4"
msgid "Mātāpitaro sukheti pīṇeti sammā sukhaṃ pariharati. "
msgstr "He makes his mother and father happy … "

# NOTE: When the phrase puttadara is resolved, as at SN 3.10, dara is plural. Also note that this kind of context shows that putta is by default “children” and should be translated as “son” only when required by the context.
msgctxt "an4.61:13.5"
msgid "Puttadāradāsakammakaraporise sukheti pīṇeti sammā sukhaṃ pariharati. "
msgstr "He makes his children, partners, bondservants, workers, and staff happy … "

msgctxt "an4.61:13.6"
msgid "Mittāmacce sukheti pīṇeti sammā sukhaṃ pariharati. "
msgstr "He makes his friends and colleagues happy … "

# NOTE: BB’s rendering of this is verbose, and much of it is a paraphrase of the comms. The idiom is hard to capture, not because the words are obscure but because they are too common and ambiguous. I take “pattagata” to mean “what has been gotten”, i.e. possessions. I take “thanagata” as a synonym. ayatanaso is “within means or scope”, i.e. suitable.
msgctxt "an4.61:13.7"
msgid "Idamassa paṭhamaṃ ṭhānagataṃ hoti pattagataṃ āyatanaso paribhuttaṃ. "
msgstr "This is his first solid and substantive investment, used in the appropriate sphere. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.68, sc14
msgctxt "an4.61:14.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, gahapati, ariyasāvako uṭṭhānavīriyādhigatehi bhogehi bāhābalaparicitehi sedāvakkhittehi dhammikehi dhammaladdhehi yā tā honti āpadā aggito vā udakato vā rājato vā corato vā appiyato vā dāyādato, tathārūpāsu āpadāsu pariyodhāya saṃvattati. "
msgstr "Furthermore, with his legitimate wealth he defends himself against threats from such things as fire, flood, rulers, bandits, or unloved heirs. "

msgctxt "an4.61:14.2"
msgid "Sotthiṃ attānaṃ karoti. "
msgstr "He keeps himself safe. "

msgctxt "an4.61:14.3"
msgid "Idamassa dutiyaṃ ṭhānagataṃ hoti pattagataṃ āyatanaso paribhuttaṃ. "
msgstr "This is his second solid and substantive investment, used in the appropriate sphere. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "an4.61:15.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, gahapati, ariyasāvako uṭṭhānavīriyādhigatehi bhogehi bāhābalaparicitehi sedāvakkhittehi dhammikehi dhammaladdhehi pañcabaliṃ kattā hoti—"
msgstr "Furthermore, with his legitimate wealth he makes five spirit-offerings: "

msgctxt "an4.61:15.2"
msgid "ñātibaliṃ, atithibaliṃ, pubbapetabaliṃ, rājabaliṃ, devatābaliṃ. "
msgstr "to relatives, guests, ancestors, king, and deities. "

msgctxt "an4.61:15.3"
msgid "Idamassa tatiyaṃ ṭhānagataṃ hoti pattagataṃ āyatanaso paribhuttaṃ. "
msgstr "This is his third solid and substantive investment, used in the appropriate sphere. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "an4.61:16.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, gahapati, ariyasāvako uṭṭhānavīriyādhigatehi bhogehi bāhābalaparicitehi sedāvakkhittehi dhammikehi dhammaladdhehi ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā madappamādā paṭiviratā khantisoracce niviṭṭhā ekamattānaṃ damenti, ekamattānaṃ samenti, ekamattānaṃ parinibbāpenti, tathārūpesu samaṇabrāhmaṇesu uddhaggikaṃ dakkhiṇaṃ patiṭṭhāpeti sovaggikaṃ sukhavipākaṃ saggasaṃvattanikaṃ. "
msgstr "Furthermore, with his legitimate wealth he establishes an uplifting religious donation for ascetics and brahmins—those who avoid intoxication and negligence, are settled in patience and gentleness, and who tame, calm, and extinguish themselves—that’s conducive to heaven, ripens in happiness, and leads to heaven. "

msgctxt "an4.61:16.2"
msgid "Idamassa catutthaṃ ṭhānagataṃ hoti pattagataṃ āyatanaso paribhuttaṃ. "
msgstr "This is his fourth solid and substantive investment, used in the appropriate sphere. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17
msgctxt "an4.61:17.1"
msgid "Sa kho so, gahapati, ariyasāvako uṭṭhānavīriyādhigatehi bhogehi bāhābalaparicitehi sedāvakkhittehi dhammikehi dhammaladdhehi imāni cattāri pattakammāni kattā hoti. "
msgstr "These are the four deeds of substance that a noble disciple does with the legitimate wealth he has earned by his efforts and initiative, built up with his own hands, gathered by the sweat of the brow. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.61:17.2"
msgid "Yassa kassaci, gahapati, aññatra imehi catūhi pattakammehi bhogā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ime vuccanti, gahapati, bhogā aṭṭhānagatā apattagatā anāyatanaso paribhuttā. "
msgstr "Whatever wealth is spent on something other than these four deeds of substance is said to be not a solid or substantive investment, and not used in the appropriate sphere. "

msgctxt "an4.61:17.3"
msgid "Yassa kassaci, gahapati, imehi catūhi pattakammehi bhogā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ime vuccanti, gahapati, bhogā ṭhānagatā pattagatā āyatanaso paribhuttāti. "
msgstr "But whatever wealth is spent on these four deeds of substance is said to be a solid and substantive investment, used in the appropriate sphere. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc18
#. VAR: bhatā → bhaṭā (s1-3)
#. VAR: bhaccā → bhaṭā bhaccā (s1-3, km) | gatā bhūtā (mr)
msgctxt "an4.61:18.1"
msgid "Bhuttā bhogā bhatā bhaccā, "
msgstr "‘I’ve enjoyed my wealth, supporting those who depend on me; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.61:18.2"
msgid "Vitiṇṇā āpadāsu me; "
msgstr "I’ve overcome losses; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.61:18.3"
msgid "Uddhaggā dakkhiṇā dinnā, "
msgstr "I’ve given uplifting religious donations; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.61:18.4"
msgid "Atho pañcabalī katā; "
msgstr "and made the five spirit-offerings. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.61:18.5"
msgid "Upaṭṭhitā sīlavanto, "
msgstr "I have looked after the ethical and "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.61:18.6"
msgid "Saññatā brahmacārayo. "
msgstr "disciplined spiritual practitioners. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.69, sc19
msgctxt "an4.61:19.1"
msgid "Yadatthaṃ bhogaṃ iccheyya, "
msgstr "I’ve achieved the purpose "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.61:19.2"
msgid "paṇḍito gharamāvasaṃ; "
msgstr "for which an astute lay person "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.61:19.3"
msgid "So me attho anuppatto, "
msgstr "wishes to gain wealth. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.61:19.4"
msgid "kataṃ ananutāpiyaṃ. "
msgstr "I don’t regret what I’ve done.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc20
#. VAR: Etaṃ → evaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an4.61:20.1"
msgid "Etaṃ anussaraṃ macco, "
msgstr "A mortal person who recollects this "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.61:20.2"
msgid "ariyadhamme ṭhito naro; "
msgstr "stands firm in the teaching of the noble ones. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.61:20.3"
msgid "Idheva naṃ pasaṃsanti, "
msgstr "They’re praised in this life, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.61:20.4"
msgid "pecca sagge pamodatī”ti. "
msgstr "and they depart to rejoice in heaven.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.61:20.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

